#. <section class="sutta" id="an5.213"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.213:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.213:0.2"
msgid "22. Akkosakavagga"
msgstr "22. Abuse"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.213:0.3"
msgid "213. Sīlasutta"
msgstr "213. Ethics"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an5.213:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā dussīlassa sīlavipattiyā."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, there are these five drawbacks for an unethical person because "
"of their failure in ethics."

msgctxt "an5.213:1.2"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "an5.213:1.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, dussīlo sīlavipanno pamādādhikaraṇaṃ mahatiṃ bhogajāniṃ "
"nigacchati."
msgstr ""
"Firstly, an unethical person loses substantial wealth on account of "
"negligence."

msgctxt "an5.213:1.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamo ādīnavo dussīlassa sīlavipattiyā."
msgstr "This is the first drawback."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an5.213:2.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, dussīlassa sīlavipannassa pāpako kittisaddo "
"abbhuggacchati."
msgstr "Furthermore, an unethical person gets a bad reputation."

msgctxt "an5.213:2.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyo ādīnavo dussīlassa sīlavipattiyā."
msgstr "This is the second drawback."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.253"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an5.213:3.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, dussīlo sīlavipanno yaññadeva parisaṃ upasaṅkamati—"
"yadi khattiyaparisaṃ, yadi brāhmaṇaparisaṃ, yadi gahapatiparisaṃ, yadi "
"samaṇaparisaṃ—avisārado upasaṅkamati maṅkubhūto."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, an unethical person enters any kind of assembly timid and "
"embarrassed, whether it’s an assembly of aristocrats, brahmins, "
"householders, or ascetics."

msgctxt "an5.213:3.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyo ādīnavo dussīlassa sīlavipattiyā."
msgstr "This is the third drawback."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an5.213:4.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, dussīlo sīlavipanno sammūḷho kālaṃ karoti."
msgstr "Furthermore, an unethical person dies feeling lost."

msgctxt "an5.213:4.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, catuttho ādīnavo dussīlassa sīlavipattiyā."
msgstr "This is the fourth drawback."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an5.213:5.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, dussīlo sīlavipanno kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā "
"apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, an unethical person, when their body breaks up, after death, is "
"reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell."

msgctxt "an5.213:5.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, pañcamo ādīnavo dussīlassa sīlavipattiyā."
msgstr "This is the fifth drawback."

msgctxt "an5.213:5.3"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā dussīlassa sīlavipattiyā."
msgstr ""
"These are the five drawbacks for an unethical person because of their "
"failure in ethics."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an5.213:6.1"
msgid "Pañcime, bhikkhave, ānisaṃsā sīlavato sīlasampadāya."
msgstr ""
"There are these five benefits for an ethical person because of their "
"accomplishment in ethics."

msgctxt "an5.213:6.2"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "an5.213:6.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, sīlavā sīlasampanno appamādādhikaraṇaṃ mahantaṃ "
"bhogakkhandhaṃ adhigacchati."
msgstr ""
"Firstly, an ethical person gains substantial wealth on account of diligence."

msgctxt "an5.213:6.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamo ānisaṃso sīlavato sīlasampadāya."
msgstr "This is the first benefit."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an5.213:7.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, sīlavato sīlasampannassa kalyāṇo kittisaddo "
"abbhuggacchati."
msgstr "Furthermore, an ethical person gets a good reputation."

msgctxt "an5.213:7.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyo ānisaṃso sīlavato sīlasampadāya."
msgstr "This is the second benefit."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an5.213:8.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, sīlavā sīlasampanno yaññadeva parisaṃ upasaṅkamati—"
"yadi khattiyaparisaṃ, yadi brāhmaṇaparisaṃ, yadi gahapatiparisaṃ, yadi "
"samaṇaparisaṃ—visārado upasaṅkamati amaṅkubhūto."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, an ethical person enters any kind of assembly bold and self-"
"assured, whether it’s an assembly of aristocrats, brahmins, householders, or "
"ascetics."

msgctxt "an5.213:8.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ bhikkhave, tatiyo ānisaṃso sīlavato sīlasampadāya."
msgstr "This is the third benefit."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an5.213:9.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, sīlavā sīlasampanno asammūḷho kālaṃ karoti."
msgstr "Furthermore, an ethical person dies not feeling lost."

msgctxt "an5.213:9.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, catuttho ānisaṃso sīlavato sīlasampadāya."
msgstr "This is the fourth benefit."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.254"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an5.213:10.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, sīlavā sīlasampanno kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā "
"sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, when an ethical person’s body breaks up, after death, they’re "
"reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm."

msgctxt "an5.213:10.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, pañcamo ānisaṃso sīlavato sīlasampadāya."
msgstr "This is the fifth benefit."

msgctxt "an5.213:10.3"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ānisaṃsā sīlavato sīlasampadāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"These are the five benefits for an ethical person because of their "
"accomplishment in ethics.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.213:10.4"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
